<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871217-0097 </DOCNO><HL> Transamerica Unit's Purchase</HL><DD> 12/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TATENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> SAN FRANCISCO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Transamerica Corp. said Transamerica Insurance Co., its property-liability unit, completed the $24.5 million purchase of a 51% interest in River Thames Insurance Co.    River Thames is a unit of London's Sedgewick Group PLC. Transamerica Corp., an insurance and financial services concern, owns a 39% interest in Sedgewick. </TEXT></DOC>